Background



Camptocamp kickstarts a new crowdfunding campaign in order to develop the Odoo Magento Connector for Odoo 8 !
We estimate that EUR 15’000.- need to be collected to start this exciting project and provide the community with a one-to-one migration development.
If we collect more than EUR 15’000.- we do have a lot of ideas to extend the features of the Odoo Magento Connector: multi-company support, synchronization jobs’ categorization for optimized performance…Feel free to also make your own suggestions by sending an email to funding@camptocamp.com !
The Odoo Magento Connector for Odoo 8 will be based on the OpenERP Magento Connector for OpenERP 7 and will have the following core features:



Compatible with Odoo 8 and the latest Magento versions (1.7 or later);


Synchronization of customers, sales orders, invoices, payment and shipping status;


Multi-Websites, multi-Stores, multi-Storeviews, and even the possibility to connect several Magento instances on the same Odoo back-end;


Multi-Warehouses, multi-Currencies and multi-Languages;


Magento typology of products supported: simple, grouped and configurable products.




It is also intended to provide the public with an update on the comprehensive developer’s technical documentation aimed to help to implement the Odoo Magento Connector for Odoo 8 best.
The previous OpenERP Magento Connector for OpenERP 7 – see: www.openerp-magento-connector.com – initally required more than 60 man-days of software development to meet the demanding needs of well-established e-commerce businesses processing between 100 to 2’000 sales orders each day. Apart from being ideally suitable for important Magento e-shops, this new-generation connector gained a huge interest among the Odoo community : hundreds of messages were exchanged between users and the supporting community of this project, and we are really proud of that !


What will be achieved with the collected funds?




Migration of the Magento connector module itself (magentoerpconnect) and adaptation of the module to the updated Odoo data model;


Migration of all the e-commerce modules used by the connector (connector-ecommerce, sale_automatic_workflow, sale_payment_method, product_m2m_categories, magentoerpconnect_options_active and magentoerpconnect_pricing);



Update of the API;


Update of the developer’s documentation;


For those who were already using the OpenERP Magento Connector for OpenERP 7: availability of an additional migration routine, which will migrate your data (associated to the connector modules) from OpenERP 7 to Odoo 8.



The project's deadline is supposed to be March 31st. Once the development work will be completed, this module will remain under an Open Source license (AGPL v3).
To benefit from a great and quality module with a solid and worldwide community support, help us now to gather the needed funds to start the development of the Odoo Magento Connector for Odoo 8 !
Again, thank you so very much for your participation and support !
